# Grow Your YouTube Channel Faster w/ “Subscribe” Links

Topics: Growth Hacks, Social Media Marketing

Most people have links to their social media accounts all over the place:

- Website navbars, footers, blog posts
- Other social media accounts
- Linktrees
- etc.

And if you do, great — but you’re missing out on some *easy wins.*

Because you’re probably linking like this: [https://youtube.com/@devinschumacher](https://youtube.com/@devinschumacher)

👇 Do this instead: 👇

Instead of linking directly to your YouTube account URL..

Use a “subscribe link” so the user gets **automatically prompted to subscribe** to your channel when the page loads!

![https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/1*pgLxrVNlq3qxceqtRzeu8A.png](https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/1*pgLxrVNlq3qxceqtRzeu8A.png)

# **How to make a YouTube “Subscribe Link”**

All you have to do to get this auto “subscribe to my channel” pop-up on page load is to add 1 simple thing to the end of the URL:

```
?sub_confirmation=1
```

So instead of this:

[https://www.youtube.com/@devinschumacher](https://www.youtube.com/@devinschumacher)

**Do this:**

[https://www.youtube.com/@devinschumacher?sub_confirmation=1](https://www.youtube.com/@devinschumacher?sub_confirmation=1)

☝ And of course, always use a [serp.ly](http://serp.ly/) link so you have better tracking on how effective your marketing is!

